1. Ascaris lumbricoides (Roundworm)
	• Structure: Large cylindrical worm; males smaller with curved tail. Eggs are thick‑shelled and knobby.
	• Stages: Egg → Larva (in lungs) → Adult (in intestine).
	• Life Cycle: Eggs in feces mature in soil → ingested → larvae hatch in intestine → migrate via blood to lungs → coughed up and swallowed → mature in intestine.
Diagnostic Form: Fertilized egg in stool.
